  <span class="title-line-2">Earned Benefits Designed for Long-Term Stability</span>
</h1>

<div class="advisory-row">
  <div class="loan-card advisory-card">
    <h2>Who VA Financing Is Typically Best For</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Eligible veterans, active-duty service members, and certain spouses</li>
      <li>Buyers wanting little to no down payment</li>
      <li>Households prioritizing affordable monthly payments</li>
      <li>Borrowers seeking flexible credit guidelines</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="loan-card advisory-card soft-warning">
    <h2>When VA May Not Be the Ideal Fit</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Borrowers purchasing non-owner-occupied properties</li>
      <li>Situations exceeding VA loan limits without entitlement coverage</li>
      <li>Buyers who may prefer to avoid funding fees</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="cta-panel">
  <h2>Strategic Use of Your VA Benefit Matters</h2>
  <p>Your VA eligibility is more than a loan option — it’s a long-term financial tool. Structuring it correctly can preserve future flexibility, reduce costs, and strengthen your housing strategy.</p>
  <a href="index.html#contact" class="cta-button">Schedule a Strategy Conversation</a>
</div>

<div class="loan-card">
  <h2>How VA Loans Fit into the Mortgage Landscape</h2>
  <p>VA loans are backed by the <strong>U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs</strong> and are designed to honor military service by expanding access to affordable homeownership. These loans reduce lender risk through a federal guarantee, which often allows more favorable terms.</p>
</div>

<div class="loan-card">
  <h2>What Makes VA Financing Different</h2>
  <p>Key benefits include no required down payment, competitive interest rates, and no monthly mortgage insurance. VA guidelines emphasize sustainable housing for those who have served.</p>
</div>

<div class="loan-card">
  <h2>How Qualification Is Evaluated</h2>
  <p>Qualification centers on Certificate of Eligibility (COE), income stability, credit profile, and property eligibility. Lenders also assess residual income to ensure long-term affordability.</p>
</div>

<div class="loan-card">
  <h2>Strategic Considerations for VA Refinancing</h2>
  <p>VA refinance options, including Interest Rate Reduction Refinance Loans (IRRRL) and cash-out refinancing, can help improve payment structure or access equity — but should align with broader financial planning.</p>
</div>

<div class="loan-card">
  <h2>Common VA Loan Structures</h2>
  <p>VA Purchase • VA IRRRL (Streamline) • VA Cash-Out Refinance</p>
</div>

</div>
